    "comment": "Rationale: The localization of a Venus-tagged latrophilin-2 in knock-in mice in Fig. 1D-G shows a dendritic expression in CA1 with a dendrite domain-specific expression in the stratum lacunosum moleculare, where CA1 neurons receive inputs from entorhinal cortex.\nFig. 3D,E shows that latrophilin-2 localizes to dendritic spines in this stratum.\n\n1/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.\n- The resolution of the localization data in Fig.3 is insufficient to claim term 'integral component of postsynaptic membrane (GO:0099055)'. This is concluded from 1) its known role as a TM protein of the plasma membrane (Lphns are cell-adhesion molecules) and 2) the effect of postsynapse specific KD of the protein. Together this makes the selected term very plausible.. Experimental description: Knock-in mice were generated.",
